avoid byte-offset collisions (CLIP_DIST locations map to offset 0 with
fixed_varying_mask=0 on Vulkan, colliding with VAR0).

For VS: remap outputs, clear compact flag, update outputs_written with
individual bits per clip distance, and call pan_nir_lower_clip_distance_vs.

For FS: scan input variables to find CLIP_DIST0/1 (inputs_read not yet
populated), remap to matching VAR slots, and call
pan_nir_lower_clip_distance_fs after IO lowering.

